         <abstract>
            <p>Because of the recent high level of inflation and the expectation of continued price changes, the accounting profession is rapidly moving toward the preparation of financial statements adjusted for general price-level changes. This article discusses the alternative adjustment techniques available, the specific adjustments made to various accounts, and demonstrates the adjustments and their effects on 3 different types of companies. The resultant effects are shown to be dramatic for each company and vastly different between companies.</p>
         </abstract>
